We don’t need to add to our homeless population — and gig workers who are losing incomes would be among the first to lose their home.
While the governor expanded eligibility for paid leave and unemployment insurance for regular employees, this should extend to gig workers who are classified as independent contractors.
We need emergency income support too.
And that’s what most other gig workers would do too, because none of us makes enough money to save up for an emergency like this.
We deserve emergency income support so we can stay afloat — and gig workers need minimum pay standards for the long run, so we have something saved before the next crisis comes.